OL,3,C'Get out of the sea' warning at Barry
OL,4,CIsland beach was 'false alarm'
OL,6,F"While we appreciate the RNLI team
OL,7,Facting quickly to try and keep
OL,8,Fvisitors to the resort safe we'd like
OL,9,Fto reassure the public that regular
OL,10,Ftesting of the water at takes place
OL,11,Fand there is currently no reason to
OL,12,Fconsider the water at Whitmore Bay to
OL,13,Fbe unsafe."
OL,15,FA spokesperson for Welsh Water said:
OL,16,F"We are aware that the monitor on our
OL,17,Foverflow at Barry indicated that it
OL,18,Fwas operating on Saturday afternoon.
